HEART POWER is knowing that I am not the only person on this planet 🌎  with needs. Back in the left photo (21) I would never of even thought about posting the right photo (23), focusing on the 'overhang' under my armpit. I would've been disgusted by it back then, zooming in on that extra bit of me & doing everything I could to change it. I wanted to be the smallest I possibly could, doing everything I could to avoid food & spending as much time as I could on the treadmill with absolutely nothing to fuel me. Now, I want to be the STRONGEST I can possibly be. I thrive off lifting heavy weights, eating all the fuel I can to give me that power in the gym & in everyday life 🏋🏼🍿 My mumma bought us all up so so healthily, teaching & educating me on health from the second I popped out. She would cook from scratch at every meal & we would all get more excited over green beans than a packet of crisps! I then changed from being super healthy to being super unhealthy, thinking green vegetables 🥒 & the odd apple was all I should be eating. I would read magazine articles like 'what a celebrity eats in a day' & it would be 1 ricecake, 2 pieces of celery & 5 grapes... that's when I started thinking that was the way to eat. I rebelled against what health goddess mumma king taught me & got sucked into this trap. 
I now train 5/6 times a week, all strength sessions with maybe 1 or 2 with some cardio thrown in. I know my body inside out & look after it like it's a packet of POPCORN! I have so much energy sometimes people think I'm high... I could lift my left-picture-self with one hand & I could probably overhead squat with that Chessie!

Girls it's all about educating yourself, understanding WHAT your body does, what workouts you LOVE & WHAT food makes you feel AMAZING. You've got this, you are not alone in any stage of your journey 💛
